Step 1) 
 
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip" 

Sudo apt install unzip 

unzip awscliv2.zip			~ Unzip the AWS CLI 

sudo ./aws/install			~ Install AWS 

Aws –version 				~ Check the version 
 
Step 2) 
 
aws configure				~ This will configure your aws cli 

AWS Access Key ID:  

AWS Secret Access Key ID:  

Default region name: eu-west-1 

Default output format: json 

 

Step 3) 
 
Check for your system's architecture. 
 
uname –m				~ This will show you your system's architecture. 

 
X86_64: 
curl "https://s3.amazonaws.com/session-manager-downloads/plugin/latest/ubuntu_64bit/session-manager-plugin.deb" -o "session-manager-plugin.deb" 
 
X86: 

curl "https://s3.amazonaws.com/session-manager-downloads/plugin/latest/ubuntu_32bit/session-manager-plugin.deb" -o "session-manager-plugin.deb" 

 

AMR64: 
curl "https://s3.amazonaws.com/session-manager-downloads/plugin/latest/ubuntu_arm64/session-manager-plugin.deb" -o "session-manager-plugin.deb" 

 

Run the command: 

sudo dpkg -i session-manager-plugin.deb 
